[Autophagy 4:1, 131‑134; 1 January 2008]; ©2008 Landes Bioscience

Views and Commentaries

1Department of Biochemistry and Cell Biology; National Institute of Infectious Disease; Tokyo, Japan; 2Department of Biochemistry; Juntendo University School of Medicine; Tokyo, Japan; 3Department of Life Sciences; Graduate School of Arts and Sciences; University of Tokyo; Meguro-ku, Japan

Key words: ubiquitylation‑like modification, Atg8/Apg8/Aut7, LC3, lipidation, Atg7, Atg3

A cytosolic form of LC3 is conjugated to phosphatidylethanolamine by Atg7, an E1-like enzyme, and Atg3, an E2-like enzyme, during autophagy. To monitor intracellular autophagosomes and autolysosomes, GFP-LC3 is a useful tool. However, GFP-LC3 can aggregate without being conjugated to phosphatidylethanolamine, especially when GFP-LC3 is transiently expressed (Kuma A, Matsui M, Mizushima N. Autophagy 2007; 3:323–8). Therefore, as a negative control, we investigated a mutant human LC3DG protein in which the C-terminal Gly120 essential for LC3-lipidation is deleted, and generated a set of expression plasmids for wild-type human LC3 and mutant LC3DG fused to either CFP, GFP, YFP, or HcRed at the N terminus. We found that the mutant LC3DG protein does not react with human Atg7 and Atg3, indicating that LC3-lipidation does not occur, and few puncta containing mutant LC3DG form under starvation conditions. As observed with wildtype HcRed-LC3, mutant HcRed-LC3DG also co-localizes with polyQ150-aggregates suggesting that the colocalization of HcRedLC3 to polyQ150-aggregates is independent of LC3-lipidation. These mutant LC3DG proteins will be useful negative controls in recognizing non-specific fluorescent protein-LC3 aggregates.

C op

It is well‑recognized that GFP‑LC3 is a convenient tool to monitor intracellular autophagosomes and autolysosomes in cultured cell lines and mouse tissues.1‑7 However, caution must be taken with regard to the puncta of LC3.8 In particular, when the protein is overexpressed, GFP‑LC3 can aggregate independent of lipidation. To recognize lipidation‑independent LC3‑puncta, usage of a nega‑ tive control should be considered. A candidate negative control is the
