Figure 1. Schematic representation of the expression vectors for wild LC3 and mutant LC3DG fused to fluorescent proteins at the N terminus. The name designated to each plasmid is shown in the left panel. The cloning of human LC3/MAP1LC3B and construction of mutant LC3DG have been (previously described in ref. 9). The pECFP-C1, pEYFP-C1, pEGFP-C1, and pHcRed-C1 vectors were purchased from Takara (Tokyo, Japan). NheI-BglII fragments encoding CFP, YFP, GFP, and HcRed were excised from pECFP-C1, pEYFP-C1, pEGFP-C1, and pHcRed-C1, respectively. Each NheI-BglII fragment encoding fluorescent protein, and BglII-SalI fragment encoding wild-type or mutant human LC3, were introduced into the NheI-XhoI site of a modified pCXN2 vector.12,13 CAG promoter, chicken b-actin promoter; TK promoter:: Neo, neomycin/G418-resistant gene under the control of the herpes simplex virus thymidine kinase promoter.

