Figure 2 (Previous page). Fluorescent protein-LC3DG fusions have defects in E1- and E2-reactions. A) Formation of E1-substrate intermediates of human LC3 fusion proteins and Atg7. Wild-type LC3 (odd lanes) or mutant LC3DG (even lanes) fused with CFP (lanes 1 and 2), GFP (lanes 3 and 4), YFP (lanes 5 and 6), or HcRed (lanes 7 and 8) were transiently expressed together with the human Atg7C576S protein in HEK293 cells. After preparation of cell lysates, total protein was separated by SDS-PAGE. Human Atg7C576S (Atg7) and E1-substrate intermediates of human Atg7C576S-LC3 fusion proteins (Atg7-LC3) were recognized by immunoblotting with an anti-human Atg7 IgG (WB anti-Atg7) (as described in ref. 10). Human LC3 fused with fluorescent proteins and E1-substrate intermediates were recognized with an anti-human LC3 IgG (WB anti-LC3) (as described in ref. 11). GFP and its variants were recognized with an anti-GFP antibody (WB anti-GFP) (TAKARA, Tokyo, Japan), and HcRed-fusion proteins were detected with an anti-HcRed antibody (WB anti-HcRed) (TAKARA). Note that E1-substrate intermediates were not observed in the even lanes. (B) Formation of E2-substrate intermediates of human LC3 fusion proteins and Atg3. Wild-type LC3 (odd lanes) or mutant LC3DG (even lanes) fused with CFP (lanes 1 and 2), GFP (lanes 3 and 4), YFP (lanes 5 and 6), or HcRed (lanes 7 and 8) was transiently expressed together with human Atg7 and GFP-hAtg3C264S in HEK293 cells. After cell lysate preparation, total proteins were separated by SDS-PAGE. Human Atg7 was recognized with an anti-human Atg7 IgG (WB anti-hAtg7). Human Atg3C264S and E2-substrate intermediates of LC3 and Atg3C264S were recognized with an anti-human Atg3 serum (WB anti-Atg3) (as described in Ref. 11). LC3 fusion proteins and E2-substrate intermediates were observed with an anti-human LC3 IgG (WB anti-LC3). The asterisk indicates a non-specific band. Note that E2-substrate intermediates were not formed in the even lanes. (C) Subcellular fractionation of cells expressing GFP-LC3, GFP-LC3DG, HcRed-LC3, and HcRed-LC3DG. Cells expressing fluorescent protein-LC3 were lysed by sonication, and the lysates (T) were centrifuged at 100,000 x g for 1 h. Proteins in the supernatant (S) and pellet (P) fractions were separated on a 4–12% NuPAGE gel. LC3-fusions were recognized by immunoblotting with an anti-LC3 IgG. The blot was also probed with an antibody against Atg7, a cytosolic protein marker, and an antibody against the endoplasmic reticulum resident protein calnexin, as a membrane-bound protein marker.

